# Obsidian Wiki Agent

An Obsidian vault template designed for AI-assisted knowledge management. Drop raw sources (PDFs, audio, docs, URLs) into `raw/`, and an LLM agent converts, summarizes, and cross-references them into a structured wiki.

## How It Works

```
raw/              ← You drop files here (immutable, agent never modifies)
wiki/
  sources/        ← Agent-generated summaries of raw sources
  entities/       ← People, places, organizations, objects
  concepts/       ← Abstract ideas, themes, theories
  index.md        ← Catalog of all wiki pages
  log.md          ← Chronological operation log
```

The agent follows the rules in `.rules` and uses two tools:

- [Markdownify MCP server](https://hub.docker.com/r/mcp/markdownify) (via Docker) — converts non-markdown sources (PDF, DOCX, audio, YouTube, web pages, …) into markdown before ingestion.
- [QMD](https://github.com/tobi/qmd) — local hybrid search engine (BM25 + vector + LLM rerank) over the vault. Used by the agent for queries, ingest cross-checks, and lint passes. Invoked via `npx @tobilu/qmd` so no global install is needed.

## Setup

**Prerequisites:**
- [Docker](https://www.docker.com/) installed and running (for Markdownify).
- [Node.js](https://nodejs.org/) >= 22 (for QMD via `npx`).

```bash
git clone https://github.com/fauzanfebrian/obsidian-wiki-agent my-vault
cd my-vault
./init.sh
```

`init.sh` will:
- Create the directory structure (`raw/`, `wiki/` subdirs).
- Scaffold `wiki/index.md` and `wiki/log.md` if missing.
- Generate a `.gitignore` that excludes raw file contents and Obsidian session state.
- Replace `<ABSOLUTE_PATH_TO_VAULT>` placeholders in `.mcp` and `.rules` with your actual path.
- Register two QMD collections (`wiki`, `raw`) and seed their path contexts.

Then:
1. Point your AI IDE to the `.mcp` file for MCP configuration (Markdownify).
2. Open the folder in Obsidian.
3. After dropping your first sources into `raw/`, build the search index:
   ```bash
   npx @tobilu/qmd update    # scan files into the index
   npx @tobilu/qmd embed     # generate vector embeddings (slower, one-time)
   ```

## Usage

Tell your agent:

- `"Ingest the PDF in raw/"` — converts, summarizes, cross-references, and re-indexes via QMD.
- `"Summarize this YouTube video: [URL]"` — fetches transcript, creates source + concept pages.
- `"Lint the wiki"` — checks for orphan pages, dead links, contradictions, missing frontmatter, topic gaps.
- `"What do we know about X?"` — agent runs `qmd query` against the vault, then synthesizes with citations.

You can also drive QMD yourself:

```bash
npx @tobilu/qmd query "project timeline" -c wiki
npx @tobilu/qmd get "wiki/concepts/some-page.md"
npx @tobilu/qmd status
```

## Files

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `.rules` | Agent instructions: operations, formatting, directory ownership, tool usage. |
| `.mcp` | MCP server config (Markdownify via Docker). |
| `init.sh` | One-time setup script (paths, scaffolding, QMD bootstrap). |
| `.obsidian/` | Obsidian settings (graph colors, core plugins). |
